<item>
            <title>[ENTESB-1570] jetty.xml in child container is not getting detected</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/ENTESB-1570</link>
                <project id="12314570" key="ENTESB">JBoss Fuse</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;SCENARIO:&lt;br/&gt;
Using fuse 6.1. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;We are trying to deploy the application using fuse Fabric.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The profile is deployed perfectly in the root container, but is failing in the child containers&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Our application needs a new entry in the jetty.xml. If a new entry does not appears in the jetty.xml the authentication module fails and the war is not deployed:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the profile that deploy the app is added to the root container, the application is deployed with no error.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When the same profile is added to a child container, then this exception appears:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://gist.github.com/dvirgiln/f4a794dc66dc74a9f602&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://gist.github.com/dvirgiln/f4a794dc66dc74a9f602&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The jetty.xml that appears in the etc folder has not been modified.&lt;br/&gt;
It has been included a new jetty.xml file in the profile folder.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Seems that if i add a file jetty.xml in the profile, it is not getting read in case of the child container.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Clarifying:&lt;br/&gt;
The jetty.xml to be used is included in the profile folder&lt;br/&gt;
The root deployment is done correctly but the child container deployment is failing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
