                            <comment id="12974884" author="kconner" created="Tue, 10 Jun 2014 09:01:25 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue is being caused by a race condition on startup between the wars being deployed and the URL Handlers getting registered.  The list of missing URL Handlers changes and we have seen zk, mvn and profile missing from that list.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;There is no need to deploy anything to see this, simply create a child container, &quot;fabric:container-create-child  root XX&quot;, using your favourite debug options and place a breakpoint on the throw at the beginning of org.apache.felix.framework.URLHandlersStreamHandlerProxy.parseURL().  Be warned that pax-web will eat the exception and fail silently, returning null for the missing configuration file.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12975543" author="gnodet" created="Thu, 12 Jun 2014 04:06:43 -0400"  >&lt;p&gt;Pushed a fix at PR&lt;br/&gt;
   &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/fabric8io/fabric8/pull/1727&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://github.com/fabric8io/fabric8/pull/1727&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
